@vittoriosandoni7064 I'm considering it from a purely bioelectrical point, if you wish.

But it irks me that no serious study has been made on the subject, if only to disprove it.

While I have close to zero knowledge on the subject, it doesn't sound implausible to me that the present of nearby low level currents could affect a plant's growth, in the same way that modifying the light patterns in an indoor setting does, for example.
